WorldStage Newsonline– Arbico Plc, a full service building and civil engineering construction company has released its earnings forecast for the second quarter (Q2) ended June 30, 2021 to the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) with projected revenue of N962 million compared with N1.067 billion in first quarter 2021 forecast. The company also projected a 49.41% drop in profit at  N14.558 million from N28.779 billion forecasted for Q1 2021. WorldStage earlier reported Arbico earnings forecast for the first quarter (Q1) ended March 31, 2021with a projected revenue of N1.067 billion compared with N1.90 billion in fourth quarter 2020.